A schoolboy has been left with serious injuries after being brutally stabbed on a double decker bus today.

The 15-year-old victim was injured during a fight involving a number of youths on board a 151 bus in Sutton, south London, at around 2.30pm.

The boy was driven to a nearby hospital where his condition was tonight described as 'serious but stable'.

